			<div id="body-content">

			<h1 class="entry-title">Inside Solid: who will build the &#8220;god platform&#8221; for the Internet of Things?</h1>

					

				

				<h2 class="subhead">Everyone is racing to build the topmost layer for home automation.</h2>

			
			

			<div class="entry-meta">				

				
					<span class="meta-sep">by</span> 	

					
						<span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" rel="author" href="http://radar.oreilly.com/jbruner" title="View all posts by Jon Bruner">

						Jon Bruner</a></span> |								

					
				<!-- RSPEAK_STOP -->

				
					<a href="http://twitter.com/JonBruner "> @JonBruner </a> |

				
				
					<a href="https://plus.google.com/u/0/101046267110900106717/posts"> +Jon Bruner</a> |

				
				
				
					<span class="comments-link utility-items"><a href="http://radar.oreilly.com/2014/09/inside-solid-who-will-build-the-god-platform-for-the-internet-of-things.html#comments" title="Comment on Inside Solid: who will build the &#8220;god platform&#8221; for the Internet of Things?"><span class="dsq-postid" rel="70819 http://radar.oreilly.com/?p=70819">Comments: 14</span></a></span>

					<span class="meta-sep utility-items"> | </span>

					

				
				<span class="entry-date">September 23, 2014</span> 				

			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

			

			<div class="entry-utility social">						

